  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "Credibility assessment for CFD-based hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) operating conditions. The model is intended to predict absolute hemolysis index values for regulatory submission supporting a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across blood viscosity, pump rotational speed, and inlet flow rate. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors were evaluated; seven factors were formally assessed and six flagged as epistemic gaps at MRL 5. Required credibility levels are elevated due to high model risk. The claim and requirement nodes below encode the intended-use scope in prose; this package conforms to ProfileMinimal and the structured Context of Use link is not separately bound.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-mrl5-vad",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou2-cfd-hemolysis-vad-class3",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-hemolysis-v2",
